data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
The small signal model equivalent circuit for a bipolar transistor consists of the large signal model plus parasitic capacitive elements:
* Collector base capacitor * Base charging capacitor and * Collector substrate capacitor
Parasitic resistive elements include the series base and series collector resistance, output resistance. Collector to base resistance is modeled by the increase in Vce due to a decrease in change of the base current. The output resistance is modeled by the change in Vce by the change in current. The transconductance is modeled by gm= dIc / dVbe. The frequency response of the small signal model is dependent on the transconductance and inversely proportional to the collector base capacitance, the base charging capacitance and the emitter base depletion layer capacitance.
The collector current increases as Vce increases. From the diagram shown on the right, for v1 value of 900mVdc, the current at 50 ohm load is 7.5mA. At 500mVdc the current at 50 ohm load is 2.46mA.
